That's a good detour given the circumstances. Write within your settings, but outside of your established canons; explore what's beyond your usual casts of characters and the plots they serve. Nobody can (draw a perfect circle). It's a running meme in every art community, if that's any consolation. But please, do consider sketching in your free time; drawing is a very effective compliment to creative writing. They're such closely related pastimes, I can say from experience that it's easy to give in and enjoy the emergent art somewhat more than the former for a while, because it tickles the same fancies that the learned art did when it once imparted those first feelings of fulfillment. I know that it can be frustrating when fulfillment undergoes one of its frequent and recurring droughts. In my case, even if my drawings aren't much, drawing itself is a huge relief from the bleak and overbearing malaise that's befallen my own creative spirit and reduced me to procrastinating on everything except things I've never done before.
